headline: 1 Semiconductor Stock with Competitive Advantages and 2 to Keep Off Your Radar
summary: Semiconductors are the silicon backbone of the digital revolution. Demand for chips is variable though, meaning that corporate inventory levels and sentiment can significantly impact the industry. Uncertainty surrounding these factors has hurt semiconductor stocks over the past six months as they have pulled back by 17%. This drawdown was noticeably worse than the S&P 500’s 1.7% fall.
